However, the procedures for review and oversight of data and sample access are not sufficiently organized to achieve the full benefits of data and sample sharing ( 
 Tiffin 
  et al., 2019
 ; 
 van Panhuis 
  et al., 2014
 ), particularly concerning international transactions of data and samples. Many attempts are being made to implement governance frameworks that are globally applicable, as well as safeguard the interests and address the concerns of all relevant parties. Such an effective framework needs to be fair, efficient, show accountability and, just as importantly, be sustainable in the long run ( 
 de Vries 
  et al., 2017
 ; 
 Klingstrom 
  et al., 2016
 ).
